Using the Maven Plugin
=======================

Step 1: Make sure the spring-boot-maven-plugin is present inside the pom.xml
Step 2: Run the command: ./mvnw clean install spring-boot:build-image
Step 3: This creates a docker image.
Step 4: You can also specify the docker image name using the configuration

this is the required plugin, it is already present by default

<build>
        <plugins>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
                <artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>
